# GitHub OAuth App credentials — required for authentication.
# Register your OAuth App at https://github.com/settings/developers
# Set the Authorization callback URL to: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback
# Instructions: docs/DEPLOYMENT.md
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=

# GitHub PATs for calibration scripts (npm run calibrate).
# Generate at: https://github.com/settings/tokens → "Generate new token (classic)"
# Required scope: public_repo (read access only) — no other scopes needed.
#
# Option 1 — Numbered (recommended for 3+ tokens, one per line):
# GITHUB_TOKEN_1=ghp_...
# GITHUB_TOKEN_2=ghp_...
# GITHUB_TOKEN_3=ghp_...
# GITHUB_TOKEN_4=ghp_...
# GITHUB_TOKEN_5=ghp_...
#
# Option 2 — Comma-separated (single line):
# GITHUB_TOKENS=ghp_token1,ghp_token2,ghp_token3
#
# Option 3 — Single token:
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
#
# Priority: numbered → comma-separated → single.
# Each additional token roughly doubles rate limit throughput.

# Dev-only server-side PAT fallback (Issue #207, constitution §III.4 v1.2).
# Set this ONLY in a local .env.local when running a non-primary worktree that
# cannot complete GitHub OAuth (e.g. a dev server bound to a port other than
# the OAuth App's registered callback). When set under `next dev`, server-side
# routes use this PAT in place of the OAuth session token and the sign-in page
# is bypassed for that local session.
#
# Rules:
#   - dev-only: server throws at boot if NODE_ENV=production and this is set.
#   - never commit this value; .env.local is gitignored.
#   - never set this in Vercel or any production environment.
#   - minimum scope: public_repo (read-only).
# DEV_GITHUB_PAT=ghp_...
